I have written and re-written this review over the last day and a half for Papa Johns pizza and decided the following: #1: shoutout to Mohamed and the team at the Coney Island Avenue spot... the recommendation of the Buffalo sauce pizza was excellent! I am so glad that I took your recommendation instead of just allowing my hatred of that red sugar sauce (masquerading as pizza marinara sauce) to be the only thing I know of Papa Johns.  The Buffalo sauce pizza is deliciously savory and spicy then add to that the onions ... and it is a good and tasty pizza (glad I didn't have the bacon with it as it might have become too salty— though bacon can make alot of things taste better). #2 I appreciate the thoughtfulness of the delivery guy. He waited patiently and with a smile — couldn't see him well, but I could definitely smell the pizza ... as could my pup who tried to get into the box as he handed it to me. Though he was not fully comfortable with my pup getting too near, he was a good sport. And finally, #3 The Buffalo pizza stands up to the “just as good to eat” test the next day... ate the rest for breakfast and lunch. I highly recommend it!
